The paper presents an algorithm for the constrained 2-means problem, which is a clustering problem. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The algorithm involves optimization and approximation techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the transformation of existing approximation schemes for the constrained k-means problem, which could make it relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
